cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper proposes a fast and accurate approximation method for Singular Value Thresholding (SVT) to solve low rank optimization problems. The proposed method is evaluated on various computer vision problems, such as subspace clustering, weather artifact removal, and simultaneous multi-image alignment and rectification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper involves developing a range propagation method, which could also fit into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
